      "name": "CFD model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions in the FDA centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model demonstrates sufficient credibility for use in identifying worst-case pump-induced hemolysis operating conditions across the five specified flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Mesh convergence, pressure-flow validation, and hemolysis index comparisons collectively support model adequacy at Model Risk Level 2. The relative hemolysis index criterion (RH < 1) is met at all operating points, and the model correctly ranks operating conditions by hemolysis severity.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; CPB operating range (2500–3500 RPM, 3–6 L/min); MRL 2 comparative assessment; Class II device regulatory submission support.",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory decision that CFD-predicted hemolysis rankings are reliable for identifying worst-case conditions without requiring exhaustive in-vitro testing of all geometric variants."
